Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. In a #medium pot{}, bring 2 1/2 cups water to a boil with the
@farro{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a large pinch of @salt{}. Once boiling,
reduce to a simmer and cook for ~{35-40%minutes}, until al dente, rinse the cold water,
and set aside.

Meanwhile, peel the @carrots{2}, quarter lengthwise, then cut into 4-inch spears. Strip the
thymestem leaves off the @thyme{1%sprig}, then roughly chop. Mince or grate the
@garlic{2%cloves}. Zest and juice the @lemon{1}.

Toss the carrots on a #baking sheet{} with 1/2 tablespoon @olive oil{3.5%tablespoon}, half
the @cumin{1%teaspoon}, the garlic, and half the thyme. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} and place in oven to cook for ~{20%minutes}, until caramelized. Set aside.

While the carrots and farro cook, make the vinaigrette. In a #large bowl{}, whisk 2
tablespoons lemon juice with 3 tablespoons olive oil, the lemon zest, and the remaining
cumin and thyme. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

In another #small bowl{}, stir 1 tablespoon of the vinaigrette into the
@sour cream{2%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Peel, pit, and thinly
slice the @avocado{1}.

Toss the farro into the remaining vinaigrette along with the roasted carrots,
@arugula{1%ounce}, and avocado. Sprinkle with the @pepitas{1%ounce} and dollop with the
sour cream mixture. Enjoy!